Rating: 4
My French mother in law makes Tarte Tatin all the time. But she cheats by using French supermarket frozen crust, cutting her prep. time by half but still getting amazing results! I always resisted making it because I hate making pie crust. But this recipe's crust is so easy and tastes fabulous! For the filling, my mother in law doesn't use any butter. Just add sugar to pan and melt until light brown. Add apples (about 4 large apples if using a regular 9-inch pan/pie dish). Cook apples in caramel until soft but still holding form -- for me far less time than this recipe calls for. I transferred to a pie dish and added foil under my pie dish to catch some overflowing caramel. Added pie crust and baked until golden brown. Perfect appearance and taste, although I did find the cooking/baking a little messy. My husband said it was as good as his mother's!

