Rating: 4
I gotta tell ya...this recipe is definitely the best one of many I've tried. The sour cream pastry is awesome and hard to screw up. The technique for carmelizing the apples is the most foolproof of them all as well. HOWEVER. This is what I found: - too sweet. I reduced the sugar/butter in the apples part by 1/3 and found it just perfect. - cooking times too long. Especially with certain cooking apples; after all, who wants mush? It took less than 1/2 hour to produce brown caramel and exactly 20 minutes to bake to perfection in my house. I am aware everybody's oven is different - but beware. Keep an eye. Otherwise go with THIS recipe as opposed to the ones that have you boiling sugar on it's own. That is just a recipe for disaster for first timers, and I think this one is much better. Enjoy.

