Rating: 3
I read all reviews and then did the following: I used the butter/shortening pastry found on the sour cherry pie (on this site) I have had success with before. I made the dough at 10. peeled 5 HUGE granny smiths at 2 pm and sprinkled with the 2 T of sugar, a dash of cinnamon, nutmeg and pepper as suggested below. I started the carmel in my 10" non stick all clad b/c that was the closest I had. Because of the dark coating I couldn't tell how dark the carmel was and was worried about burning issues as suggested below. I did the carmel w/o apples for about 3 min. but I think next time i'll do longer. I fitted as many apples in as i could, but had problems with the last few. I cooked on stove for about 40 min. and let it cool slightly as I was ahead of schedule. I think this was a mistake b/c I do think the bottom apples were cooked too much, though the top ones that i had fitted in 1/2 way through stove cooking were just right. Then i cut out pastry (perfect!) baked for 30 min at 400 (my oven runs hot) and it looked gorgeous. had no problems with it coming out using the nonstick. Only lessons for next time: more carmel w/o apples, about 35 min. on stove and top with pastry and bake w/o cooling down in between (b/c the apples continued to cook, o/c).

